Japanese: 踏み入れることを許された彼の地は
English: Those who set foot in this land...
French: Ceux qui posent pied sur cette terre...
Italian: Chi mette piede in questo posto
Russian: Те, кто зайдут в эти земли...
TraditionalChinese: 自此處容許外人進入時

Japanese: 萌える樹も 湧く水も 朽ちた蹟も
Spanish:
... que deja sin aliento
a quien en él se adentre.
Korean: 싹트는 나무도 샘솟는 물도 쇠퇴한 자취도
TraditionalChinese: 茂密的樹林 噴湧的水泉 及老朽的遺跡

Japanese: 集うものたちを招き入れる地となろう
English: Ancient ruins, lush greens, and rich waters.
French:
Ruines anciennes, végétation luxuriante
et eaux riches.
Italian:
Tra rovine vetuste, acque feconde
e verde rigoglioso.
German:
Uralte Ruinen, üppiges Grün
und reichhaltige Gewässer.
Spanish:
Rebosante de ruinas, exuberante
vegetación y caudalosas corrientes.
Russian:
Древние руины, пышная зелень
и обильные воды.
Polish:
Prastare ruiny, bujna zieleń i bogate
wody.
PortugueseBr:
Ruínas ancestrais, verde luxuriante
e águas ricas.
TraditionalChinese: 都將成為眾人聚集之地吧
Arabic: أطلال قديمة، وخضراء مورقة، ومياه غنية.

Japanese: 広がり止まぬ、樹と蹟の秘境
TraditionalChinese: 伸展無盡 樹與遺跡之秘境
SimplifiedChinese: 树木古迹 无限秘境
